    "description": "UNIVA Oak Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides management support services to various businesses in Japan. It operates through nine segments: Growth Support Business; Beauty and Healthcare Business; Renewable Energy Business; Digital Marketing Business; Media Business; Sports Business; Resort Business; Restaurant Revitalization Business; and Shared Service Business. The company offers equity finance underwriting, merger and acquisition support, consulting, and corporate management issues resolution services; designs and sells beauty and health products; and installs and sells solar power generation equipment; and provides Gyro-n, a website improvement tool for digital marketing. It also broadcasts radio programs, organizes events, and produces various content; manages Royal Basketball League, an urban sports professional league for 3x3 basketball; operates Makani Golf Club, a golf course; engages in the renovation of restaurants; and undertakes back-end operations, including general affairs, human resources, accounting, and finance of companies. The company was formerly known as Oak Capital Corporation and changed its name to UNIVA Oak Holdings Limited in October 2023. UNIVA Oak Holdings Limited was founded in 1868 and is headquartered in Minato, Japan."
